            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">4.00</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">4.25</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">4.50</tablecol>
          </tablerow>
          <tablerow>
            <tablecol valign="top">Child</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">1.75</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">2.00</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">2.00</tablecol>
          </tablerow>
          <tablerow>
            <tablecol valign="top">Bus Lunch</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">3.25</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">4.25</tablecol>
            <tablecol align="right" valign="top">4.50</tablecol>
          </tablerow>
          <tablerow>
            <tablecol colspan="4" valign="top">Circumstances may arise in which a discount in excess of the group rates may be authorized<br/> at the Manager's discretion (e.g.: a tour company bringing in large groups).</tablecol>
          </tablerow>
        </table>
        <regnote>
          <strong>Note:</strong> this regulation replaces B.C. Reg. 121/91.</regnote>
        <provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <actname>Heritage Conservation Act</actname>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 187, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 37]</provisionsnote>
      </content>
